account_home.overview.http_requests_tool: Requests for your web content (pages, files). A single visit requires many HTTP requests to load your website or app. Cloudflare caches this content to load your site faster, and shields your origin server from malicious or unwanted requests.
account_home.overview.bandwidth_tooltip: The total volume of data, measured in bytes, sent from the Cloudflare network to a client when they request content from your domain. This represents your egress (outgoing) traffic.
account_home.overview.visits_tooltip: Visits from unique IP addresses to your domains. Includes bots, plugins, or APIs consuming partial content (but not loading a full page).
account_home.overview.page_views_tooltip: A subset of HTTP requests, filtered to successful text/HTML document requests (page loads). Does not include subsequent requests for assets (JS, CSS, images, APIs).
account_home.overview.access_logins_tool: The number of successful logins to applications protected by Cloudflare Access.
account_home.overview.gateway_requests_t: Includes all DNS and HTTP requests evaluated by Gateway security and filtering policies.
account_home.overview.cache_rate_tooltip: Percentage of requests served from Cloudflare cache rather than hitting your servers. A low cache rate often means your caching configuration or origin cache-control headers are restricting or bypassing Cloudflare cache.
